
###Block:
Empathic Link		KEY:Dragon Companion ~ Empathic Link		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Dragon Companion.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The druid has an empathic link with the dragon companion to a 1 mile distance. The druid can communicate empathically with the dragon companion, but cannot see through its eyes. Because of the link's limited nature, only general emotions can be shared. The druid has the same connection to an item or place that his dragon companion does.
Share Spells		KEY:Dragon Companion ~ Share Spells			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Dragon Companion.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The druid may cast a spell with a target of "You" on her dragon companion (as a spell with a range of touch) instead of on herself. A druid may cast spells on her dragon companion even if the spells normally do not affect creatures of the companion's type (dragon). Spells cast this way must come from a class that grants an animal companion. This ability does not allow the druid to share abilities that are not spells, even if they function like spells. If the character has levels in cavalier, he can exchange this ability for Light Armor Proficiency. Once this choice is made, it cannot be changed.
Deliver Touch Spells	KEY:Dragon Companion ~ Deliver Touch Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Dragon Companion.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A dragon companion can deliver touch spells for the druid. If the druid and the dragon companion are in contact at the time the druid casts a touch spell, he can designate the dragon companion as the "toucher." The dragon companion can then deliver the touch spell just as the druid would. As usual, if the druid casts another spell before the touch is deliver, the touch spell dissipates. If the character has levels in cavalier, he can exchange this ability for evasion, as the rogue class feature. Once this choice is made, it cannot be changed.
Ability Score Increase	KEY:Dragon Companion ~ Ability Score Increase	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Dragon Companion.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:The dragon companion adds +1 to one of its ability scores at the indicated levels.
Bonus Dragon Feat		KEY:Dragon Companion ~ Bonus Dragon Feat		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Dragon Companion.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:A dragon companion gains a dragon feat as a bonus feat at the indicated levels. The dragon companion must meet the feat's prerequisites in order to select it.	DEFINE:Pool_Bonus_Dragon_Feat|0	BONUS:VAR|Pool_Bonus_Dragon_Feat|(MasterLevel>=3)+(MasterLevel>=6)+(MasterLevel>=10)+(MasterLevel>=14)+(MasterLevel>=18)
Spell Resistance		KEY:Dragon Companion ~ Spell Resistance		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Dragon Companion.SpecialQuality	SOURCEPAGE:p.	DESC:If the druid is 11th level or higher, a dragon companion gains spell resistance equal to the druid's level + 5. To affect the dragon companion with a spell, another spellcaster must get a result on a caster level check (1d20 + caster level) that equals or exceeds the dragon companion's spell resistance.	SR:5+MasterLevel

